What is a component in angular
Components are the basic buiding blocks of an angular application. It's the one of the key features of an angular application.
Angular is a compoennt - based architecture. It divides the application into smaller and re-usable user interfaces called compoennts.
A component is a typscripte class which contains methods and properties to be consumed by html template/view.

import {compoennt} from '@angular/core';

@compoennt({
selector: "app-root"
templateUrl: "/app.component.html"
styleUrls: [/app.compoennt.scss]
})

export class AppComponent {
title: string = "Hello";
}
